{"cursor":"41405","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Taxobox\n| name = Asiatic lion status = EN status_system=iucn3.1 status_ref =  trend = stable image = The Asiatic Lion.jpg image_width =\n| image_caption =Male image2= Asiatic.lioness.arp.jpg image2_width=\n| image2_caption=Female regnum = Animalia phylum = Chordata classis = Mammalia\n| ordo = Carnivora familia = Felidae genus = [[Panthera]] species = [[Panthera\n| leo|P. leo]] subspecies = 'P. l. persica' trinomial = Panthera leo persica\n| trinomial_authority = Meyer, 1826 synonyms = P. l. asiaticus, P. l.\n| goojratensis range_map = Map Guj Nat Parks Sanctuary.png\n| range_map_caption = Current distribution of the Asiatic lion in the wild\n}} The 'Asiatic lion' (Panthera leo persica), also known as the 'Indian lion',\nis a lion subspecies that exists as a single isolated population in India's\nGujarat State. It is listed as ''Endangered'' by IUCN based on the small\npopulation size. The lion population has steadily increased\nin Gir Forest National Park, more than doubling from a low of 180 individuals in\n1974 to a level of 411 individuals consisting of 97 adult males, 162 adult\nfemales, 75 sub-adults, and 77 cubs as of April 2010.\n\nThe Asiatic lion was first described by the Austrian zoologist Johann N. Meyer\nunder the trinomen Felis leo persicus. Meyer, J. N. (1826). Dissertatio\ninauguralis anatomico-medica de genere felium. Doctoral thesis, University of\nVienna. It is one of the five big cats found in India, apart from Bengal\ntiger, Indian leopard, snow leopard and clouded leopard.\nIt formerly occurred in Persia, Mesopotamia, Baluchistan, from Sind in the west\nto Bengal in the east, and from Rampur and Rohilkund in the north to Nerbudda in\nthe south. It differs from the African lion by less inflated auditory bullae, a\nlarger tail tuft and a less developed mane. Pocock, R. I.\n(1939).\n[http://www.archive.org/stream/PocockMammalia1/pocock1#page/n261/mode/2up The\nFauna of British India, including Ceylon and Burma. Mammalia. â Volume 1].\nTaylor and Francis Ltd., London. pp. 212â222\n","linknr":680,"url":"Asiatic_lion","recorded":1374768189,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Asiatic_lion&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Asiatic_lion&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/File:The_Asiatic_Lion.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2e/The_Asiatic_Lion.jpg/220px-The_Asiatic_Lion.jpg","/wiki/File:Asiatic.lioness.arp.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/dd/Asiatic.lioness.arp.jpg/220px-Asiatic.lioness.arp.jpg","/wiki/Conservation_status","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/70/Status_iucn3.1_EN.svg/220px-Status_iucn3.1_EN.svg.png","/wiki/Endangered_species","/wiki/IUCN_Red_List","#cite_note-iucn-1","/wiki/Biological_classification","/wiki/Animal","/wiki/Chordate","/wiki/Mammal","/wiki/Carnivora","/wiki/Felidae","/wiki/Panthera","/wiki/Panthera_leo","/wiki/Trinomen","/w/index.php?title=Johann_Nepomuk_Meyer&action=edit&redlink=1","/wiki/File:Map_Guj_Nat_Parks_Sanctuary.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/64/Map_Guj_Nat_Parks_Sanctuary.png/220px-Map_Guj_Nat_Parks_Sanctuary.png","/wiki/Synonym_(taxonomy)","#cite_n